# Style Guide: Company Details Card

## Typography
**Headings**S
Card Title: text-lg (18px) with font-semibold
Section Labels: text-sm (14px) with font-semibold
**Body Text**
Description Text: text-sm (14px)
Text Color: Default for labels, text-muted-foreground for descriptions

## Spacing
**Card Container**
Outer Padding: p-2
Header Bottom Padding: pb-6
**Content Spacing**
Between Major Sections: space-y-8 (32px)
Between Elements: space-y-4 (16px)
Between Related Items: space-x-2 (8px) for horizontal spacing

## Buttons
**Dimensions**
Height: h-8
Padding: px-3
Text Size: text-xs
**Icons**
Size: w-3 h-3
Margin Right: mr-2
**States**
Default: size="sm"
Transitions: transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out

## Colors
**Backgrounds**
- Card Background: bg-white
- Parent Container: bg-gray-100/75
**Text Colors**
- Primary Text: Default theme color
- Secondary Text: text-muted-foreground

## Example Implementation
```
<Card className="w-full bg-white p-2">
  <CardHeader className="pb-6">
    <CardTitle className="text-lg font-semibold">Section Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <div className="space-y-8">
      <div className="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold">Label</h3>
          <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Description text</p>
        </div>
        <Button 
          size="sm" 
          className="h-8 text-xs px-3 transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"
        >
          <Icon className="w-3 h-3 mr-2" />
          Button Text
        </Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

## Usage Guidelines
- Maintain consistent spacing between related elements
- Use semibold text for interactive or label elements
- Keep button sizes compact but clickable
- Ensure proper contrast with white card on light gray background
- Apply transitions for interactive elements